Building from Source:
===================================

Prerequisites:
	A C++ compiler that supports OpenMP

To build from source:
	This project uses CMake.  Follow the standard instructions for a CMake Project as found on the CMake website.  

	Unix
		If you are on a unix based architecture the following commands will enable you to build and run the library and the examples

		cd /path/to/source/code
		mkdir build
		cd build
		cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
		make all

		Then, you can run the examples.  Alternately, use kdevelop or another system.

	Windows
		Run cmake gui
		Point the "source directory" to the source code
		Point the "binary directory" to a new directory "build"
		press "configure" twice, then press "generate"
		Open the project file in the "binary directory" and compile the project
